  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion criteria:

          1. at chronic stage (6 months after the onset of stroke) with a pure unilateral motor
             paresis after a stroke (ischemic or hemorrhagic);

          2. sufficient cognition to follow simple instructions as well as understand the content
             and purpose of the study;

          3. able to sit up for 45 minutes (with or without assistance), and have muscle strength
             grade from 1 to 3 in the abductor pollicis brevis and extensor digitorum in the
             affected side.

        Exclusion criteria:

          1. Patients with severe dysphasia (either expressive or comprehensive) with inadequate
             communication;

          2. any additional medical or psychological condition affecting their ability to comply
             with the study protocol;

          3. history of other neurological disease, psychiatric disorder, including alcoholism and
             substance abuse.
      </textblock>
